  "root_text": {
    "sn31.4-12:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 31.4–12 ",
    "sn31.4-12:0.2": "1. Gandhabbavagga ",
    "sn31.4-12:0.3": "Sāragandhādidātāsuttanavaka ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.2": "Ekamantaṁ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.3": "“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā sāragandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ …pe… ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.4": "pheggugandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.5": "tacagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.6": "papaṭikagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.7": "pattagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.8": "pupphagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.9": "phalagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.10": "rasagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.11": "gandhagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ sahabyataṁ upapajjatī”ti? ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.12": "“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena sucaritaṁ carati, vācāya sucaritaṁ carati, manasā sucaritaṁ carati. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.13": "Tassa sutaṁ hoti: ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.14": "‘sāragandhe adhivatthā devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.15": "Tassa evaṁ hoti: ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.16": "‘aho vatāhaṁ kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā sāragandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ …pe… ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.17": "pheggugandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.18": "tacagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.19": "papaṭikagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.20": "pattagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.21": "pupphagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.22": "phalagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.23": "rasagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.24": "gandhagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ sahabyataṁ upapajjeyyan’ti. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.25": "So dātā hoti sāragandhānaṁ …pe… ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.26": "so dātā hoti pheggugandhānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.27": "so dātā hoti tacagandhānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.28": "so dātā hoti papaṭikagandhānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.29": "so dātā hoti pattagandhānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.30": "so dātā hoti pupphagandhānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.31": "so dātā hoti phalagandhānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.32": "so dātā hoti rasagandhānaṁ … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.33": "so dātā hoti gandhagandhānaṁ. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.34": "So kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā gandhagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ sahabyataṁ upapajjati. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.35": "Ayaṁ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṁ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā gandhagandhe adhivatthānaṁ devānaṁ sahabyataṁ upapajjatī”ti. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.36": "Dvādasamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn31.4-12:0.1": "Linked Discourses 31.4–12 ",
    "sn31.4-12:0.2": "1. Centaurs ",
    "sn31.4-12:0.3": "Nine Discourses On Givers of Fragrant Heartwood, Etc. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.2": "Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha: ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.3": "“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the gods who live in fragrant heartwood … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.4": "softwood … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.5": "bark … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.6": "sprouts … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.7": "leaves … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.8": "flowers … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.9": "fruit … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.10": "sap … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.11": "fragrant scents?” ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.12": "“Mendicant, it’s when someone does good things by way of body, speech, and mind. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.13": "And they’ve heard: ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.14": "‘The gods who live in fragrant heartwood … fragrant scents are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’ ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.15": "They think: ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.16": "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of the gods who live in fragrant heartwood … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.17": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.18": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.19": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.20": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.21": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.22": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.23": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.24": "fragrant scents!’ ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.25": "They give gifts of fragrant heartwood … ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.26": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.27": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.28": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.29": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.30": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.31": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.32": "",
    "sn31.4-12:1.33": "fragrant scents. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.34": "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods who live in fragrant scents. ",
    "sn31.4-12:1.35": "This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the gods who live on fragrant scents.” "
  },
